result.execSummary:
The defendant Traven J. Koenigs was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property (Over $2500) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime, Repeater, Penalties for Felonies-Class "I" Felony], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(2)(d).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant to pay supervision fees as determined by the Department Of Corrections.

miscConds.notes:
$5000.00 bond to be applied to the restitution.
$500.00 bond from case 2015CF119 to be applied to the restitution.
Restitution joint and several with co-actors.
Defendant to pay $100.00 per month on the restitution commencing May 31, 2015 and every end of month there after.
If probation is discharged/revoked with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due and/or other collection procedures will be implemented.  If revoked and sent to prison, DOC shall withhold monies to pay fines/costs/surcharges/restitution with the balance due as a condition of extended supervision/parole.
Defendant to submit to a DNA swab and pay the surcharge.
Defendant to get and maintain full time employment.

Defendant to have no contact with the victims apart from a letter of apology to the probation agent within 30 days.
Defendant to complete counseling as recommended by the probation agent.

timeConds.notes:
Defendant granted huber work release privileges with out of county travel.  Defendant may serve this jail sentence in any county that is available.
Defendant granted child care release.
